  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether rapid on-site cytopathologic evaluation
      (ROSE) can increase the diagnostic yield of transbronchial needle aspiration (TBNA) in the
      diagnosis of hilar and mediastinal lymphadenopathy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
